About Event:
ETH Denver 2024 will be taking place from February 19-March 3 at the #BUIDLHub and the $Spork Castle in Downtown Denver.

With the genesis of SporkDAO in June of 2021, ETHDenver became the first event DAO in the world. All event proceeds are used to #BUIDL value for our community and to realize the decentralized future.
‍
2024 is The Year of the SporkWhale. SporkWhales are peak contributors to the SporkDAO ecosystem. They #BUIDL, submit projects, create, and frolic in the Bufficorn Sea. Known for their large troves of $SPORK, SporkWhales are indeed a curious and fantastical member of the Bufficorn family.

SporkDAO’s ETHDenver #BUIDLathon is about gathering like-minds around a common purpose. Distributed computing is the future, and Colorado is a leading community supporting this emerging technology.

‍Our goal is empowering the Web3 community to shape this new world while cementing the Rocky Mountain region and the state of Colorado as a thriving hub of Ethereum and blockchain innovation.

STFU & Party is a travel agency specializing in once-in-a-lifetime experiences. We started this company with the goal of planning some of the most unforgettable trips at the most exciting destinations.

We know group trips are hard to plan and we understand that sometimes things can get confusing... Don't worry we are here to help! When you book our trips or customize your own experience with us, you and your group will have a streamlined trip so you can relax and enjoy.

We customize itineraries to suit your group's needs, leverage our relationships in the travel and entertainment industry to offer you the best rates and VIP access possible, and execute your dream trips from start to finish - providing a central place for your group to pay with payment plan options and split payments, choose roommates, and input traveler information.

LVL UP EXPO brings together people of all backgrounds to inspire creativity, passion, and competitive spirits on a dynamic global platform. Our annual event is a blend of competitive gaming, inspired artistry, and inclusive community-building over the course of three days and nights.

Ultra Music Festival is the world's premier electronic music festival, boasting elite DJs and top tier production located in the beautiful city of Miami, Florida. Taking place this year on March 22-24, Ultra is the best place to experience unparalleled electronic music and have the time of your life.

The TYR Wodapalooza (WZA) began as a grassroots single-day fitness competition with 145 athletes and 500 spectators in 2012 and has since established itself as the world’s premier Functional Fitness Festival. Wodapalooza descends on Miami’s Bayfront Park for 4-days in January and brings together thousands of athletes, spectators, and fitness fanatics to celebrate fitness, community, and life.

There are multiple parts to WZA Miami – the fitness competition for all backgrounds and levels (the foundation of WZA), the Gauntlet (an exciting and fast race through three workouts within an hour), and the spectator experience, which includes one of the largest collections of vendors and exhibitors as well as spectator workouts and seminars.

All set next to the Biscayne Bay in sunny Miami, the TYR Wodapalooza has become a calendar staple for the fitness community and a winter getaway for athletes from around the world.

The Premiere Conference for the Festival Industry in North America since 2015: We have tackled issues ranging from ticketing, sponsorship, talent buying, programming, sustainability, safety, marketing and more with panels, contests, keynotes and case studies. FestForums has been held in Santa Barbara, NYC and San Francisco. Live music, film premieres, cooking demos and wine tastings are also our trademark entertainment!

Barefoot Country Music Fest™, (BCMF), Jersey’s Original Country Music Beach Fest, is located in Wildwood, NJ, between the famous Morey’s Piers on the beach. BCMF is host to the industry’s biggest stars with 40+ artists slated for June 20-23, 2024, bringing a unique blend of today’s country headliners, regional stars, up-and-comers, and locals favorites performing across 5 stages. With the combination of country music and the scenic Wildwood’s backdrop, this family-friendly, four-day fest is THE summer vacation destination.

Get your paddle ready! Touted as the largest pickleball festival and tournament in the world, The Pickle Games Miami brings a 100-court pickleball tournament to the iconic Miami Marine Stadium overlooking Biscayne Bay and Downtown Miami. The weekend-long festival also includes VIP fan experiences, specialty vendors, music performance, curated food experiences and more. All levels of players, from amateurs to pros, are welcome to participate. Early bird registration is now open.

Vibra Urbana is a 2-day festival taking place on February 17-18 , 2024 at the Miami-Dade County Fair & Expo, located at 10901 SW 24th ST Miami, FL 33165. The venue opens at 1 PM both days with shows taking place rain or shine. No re-entry into the event is permitted. All ages are welcome in General Admission areas, but the VIP/Leyenda tickets are for people 21+. Food and beverages are sold separately throughout the festival grounds with many different options, so there's something for everybody. All lineup, set times, festival hours, and venue are subject to change without notice, and curfew will be at 11 PM on both festival nights.

Dubbed as the biggest Hip Hop festival in the world, Rolling Loud produced their first festival in 2015. This years California event will be taking place at the Hollywood Park Grounds, adjacent from SoFi Stadium. The 2024 lineup has been announced and includes Nicki Minaj, Post Malone, Future x Metro Boomin as Headliners, while the lineup includes artists like Party Next Door, Big Sean, Summer Walker, Don Toliver, Bryson Tiller and more!

Event Name: South Beach Wine and Food Festival
About Event: Food Network South Beach Wine & Food Festival presented by Capital One (SOBEWFF®) is a national, star-studded, four-day destination event showcasing the talents of the world’s most renowned wine and spirits producers, chefs and culinary personalities. The Festival takes place February 22 – 25, 2024. Every year, this five-day February event attracts many of the big names in the food and beverage industry, from celebrity sommeliers to chefs and culinary personalities. Since it has started, the fest has grown into a world of tastings, seminars, brunches, dinners, lunches, and parties. All net proceeds from the Festival benefit the Florida International University Chaplin School of Hospitality & Tourism Management.

Held annually each spring in Raleigh, Dreamville Festival is an outdoor weekend music celebration curated by internationally-acclaimed hip-hop superstar J. Cole alongside his Dreamville team.

The festival serves as Dreamville’s signature annual event for its fans worldwide bringing together local residents and travelers alike to gather together and enjoy incredible music performances in one of America’s most beautiful and historic public parks, Dorothea Dix Park – Raleigh’s largest city park with over 300 acres of sprawling greenspace.

As one of the most anticipated annual events in the state of North Carolina, the festival acts as a perfect complement to the existing event landscape and cultural fabric of the city of Raleigh.

As a proud Black-owned music festival, Dreamville continues to emphasize community, diversity, and inclusivity throughout the onsite fan experience each spring.

If you’ve never been, imagine a large-scale multi-stage festival featuring performances from some of the biggest names in music merged with a family-style cookout where everyone feels welcome and has a seat at the table. ALL are welcome at Dreamville Festival!

In this same spirit, J. Cole regularly invites his favorite musical artists and collaborators from across the world to perform in his home state of North Carolina – some of whom are performing for their first time ever in Raleigh – while the festival plays host to dozens of local independently-owned businesses, as well as artisans, muralists, merchants, and community organizations to offer attendees a true taste of the good life in Raleigh.

Beyond the cultural impact that Dreamville Festival creates, the weekend celebration has also become well-known for meticulously curating each year a new music lineup unlike any other, blending together stadium headliners alongside exciting up-and-comers.

Notable past performers to have graced the festival’s main stages include the biggest names in hip-hop and R&B, with a mix of established touring acts, rare on-stage reunions, and exciting up-and-comers.

The festival marks an annual reunion for Dreamville Records as J. Cole taps the entire roster to perform at the fest including Ari Lennox, Bas, J.I.D, EarthGang, Cozz, and Omen, plus Lute who hails from nearby Charlotte. With performances that highlight their latest chart-topping projects, plus old-school throwbacks and unreleased music, this festival is truly a DREAM come true for any day-one Dreamville fans.

Having grown up nearby in Fayetteville, J. Cole and his Dreamville team use the festival as an annual opportunity to shine a light on the special place that helped shape him into the successful and creative artist he is today.

Since launching in 2018, Dreamville Festival has become one of the largest annual events in the state of North Carolina as well as one of today’s most popular artist-led music festivals in the world, with guests regularly traveling from across the globe and all 50 U.S. states to attend this one-of-a-kind music experience.

Dreamville Festival today generates millions of dollars each year for the local and North Carolina economy, while providing a positive and substantial cultural impact on Raleigh and the surrounding areas that lasts long after the festival wraps up each spring.

Good Vibez Presents and PR Entertainment, Inc., the teams behind Tahoe's ever-popular Lake Tahoe Reggae Festival, are bringing the warm reggae vibes in the middle of the snow season to the Lake Tahoe Winter Reggae Festival 2024 at the brand new Tahoe Blue Event Center in Stateline, Nevada. The combination of this year's lineup, reggae vibes, stunning winter landscapes, and the warmth and excitement of the local community over the holiday weekend creates a truly magical experience that we can all look forward to.  We can't think of a better pairing than hitting the slopes in the morning followed by grooving to reggae in the evenings.

"'Holo Holo' means to travel, to sail, to move," says O'ahu-born Good Vibez co-owner, Dan Sheehan. This familiar expression is most often heard between friends as in 'let's holo holo up country', Sheehan says, when detailing the festival's origin. The inaugural Holo Holo Music Festival took place in Northern California at Frost Amphitheater at Stanford University in 2022, but "this event desires movement, so carrying Holo Holo to Las Vegas and Sacramento in 2023 was a natural progression for its fluidity."

In 2024, Holo Holo Music Festival will be taking place at the Downtown Las Vegas Events Center from April 26-28.

Florida Groves is a music and art festival that takes place over two days in Orlando, Florida. Throughout the whole experience, you'll get to enjoy the sweet sounds of world-renowned DJs, as well as amazing artists from different parts of the planet rocking the stage in multiple genres. In 2024 it will be taking place at the Orlando Central Fairgrounds on April 13 and 14.

To enjoy the roots of California's legendary music scene, this is the festival that you need to attend. The California Roots Music and Arts Festival is a three day affair held every May on the Monterey Fairgrounds that showcases some of the best bands and artists from around the Golden State. Join us on May 24-26 for an unforgettable experience.

The vision of the Great Outdoors Comedy Festival is and will always be to create an inclusive and safe experience that celebrates and features all forms of performance comedy, from locals to superstars; all while celebrating and supporting the communities and beautiful parks we visit.
VELD Music Festival is the largest annual electronic dance music festival in Canada, held at Downsview Park in Toronto, Ontario.
The funniest week in Nashville makes its 10th annual return, April 2024. Check out this year's lineup of world class comedians, tickets available now.

Event Name: Voices of America Country Music Fest
About Event: Experience a gathering of country music's greatest legends for 3 days of live performances in West Chester and celebrate the region's rich history. The Voices of America Country Music Fest is a celebration of American legacy for years to come. From world famous musical performances to a selection of different activities and more, VOA Country Music Fest is like no other show in the world.

Catch us at the Algarve!

When it comes to festival venues, we’re winning every time! Praia Da Rocha, Portimão is for the lovers of breathtaking views, golden hour & the glistening sea. Portimão is a huge tourism hub. Restaurants, nightlife, stunning hotels and villas, historic sites and more, there’s really something for everyone. Praia Da Rocha is the town’s main beach. The red-rock cliffs that surround it show they were playing no games giving it the name “Rocky Beach” in Portuguese.

III Points returns to Mana Wynwood for two days of music, art, and technology. Featuring the most premier musicians across a variety of genres, III Points is one of the most premier music festivals in all of the world.

Traditionally, a Railbird is a horse racing enthusiast known for sticking close to the action, hanging on the rail as each contender comes barreling down the track.

For one special weekend in June the term takes on an added meaning during the Annual Railbird Festival. In 2 days and on 3 stages, world class artists meet in Lexington, Kentucky to put on a one of a kind Country Music show.

Railbird takes place at Red Mile Gaming & Racing, right in the heart of Downtown. Book your trip to experience world class musical performances, delicious food, and so much more.

ACL Festival features a diverse lineup of acts every year with 9 stages, 100+ performances — and best of all, two weekends. Choose from tacos, brews, vegan options and more. The ACL Eats Food Court offers the most delicious festival food, drinks and sweets from Austin and the surrounding area’s favorite restaurants. There’s plenty to do in between sets, including a mini-fest for kids, photogenic spaces, sponsored giveaways and merch to bring home with you.

Oceans Calling is a three day festival in partnership with musicians O.A.R. featuring over 30 performances on 3 stages, all on the classic Ocean City Boardwalk. Experience world class musical performances, many different delicious food options, and so much more all on the Boardwalk.

The inaugural Minnesota Yacht Club Festival will take place at Harriet Island Regional Park in the heart of downtown St. Paul, Minnesota. Experience sound waves underneath the giant cottonwoods & along the majestic Mississippi River.

The first-ever festival will bring fans together for two days of performances across two stages with no overlapping sets between the 20 artists. No schedule conflicts on this river bank!

Check out all the festival has to offer with premium ticket options. Enjoy historic riverboat rides, comfortable lounges, exclusive food options, air-conditioned restrooms, and more!

Boston Calling Music Festival is a 3 day, 4 stage, outdoor festival featuring the biggest and best acts in live music and DJs. With visual arts and a 100 foot ferris wheel - there's so much to explore and see at Boston Calling.
